subSubSection.paragraph:
There is some inconsistency between the original description (
Fairmaire 1881
) and redescription (
Dillon and Dillon 1952
) of this rarely collected species. The latter states that the pronotum is much narrower anteriorly than at base and possesses a tubercle on each side, however our examination of a specimen matching the original 
description
reveals the pronotum to be quadrate, without lateral tubercles. The large size of this species, along with the quadrate pronotum and opaque integument are distinctive. This species is endemic to Fiji and known only from Viti Levu. Specimens have been collected from August through October, mostly at lights (
Dillon and Dillon 1952
).
